{
  "stem": "27767.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] actually, my brother Adolph, he was-- he went to four years to-- to learn in the Sheba in, in Cluj.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he got-- he got, actually, the-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] as a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He became a rabbi, actually.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He didn't work as a rabbi, but he had the title.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that point, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we were in the school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took us once a week.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They called it [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we did some work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But not-- we did some work once a week, different type of--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For the Hungarian, cleaning parks or something, not-- nothing special.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just the Jewish children, but that was later on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And especially in the winter, they took, like I said, to snow shoveling-- Jewish people, just Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after '40?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, in '40, I was 15 years old, actually, in 1940 when the Hungarians came in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was actually not 15 even.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember the Germans came in on March 22nd, 1944.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the next day, some of the army units came to our town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "German army units, they went to Budapest first.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the next day, they were in our town, some of the units.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Hungarian authorities-- because in 1940, when they came in, they put all Hungarians to the city, to the police-- the mayor, the police captain, everybody, all Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They brought Hungarians forms main Hungary.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And all the Romanians, they threw out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and-- when they came in, the Germans, the next day, the mayor-- and I mean the police-- they put some of the German officers to Jewish homes-- into Jewish homes.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
